article.headline: UNC-Greensboro 80, Cent. Arkansas 62
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Kevin Oleksiak scored 28 points to lead North Carolina-Greensboro to an 80-62 victory against Central Arkansas on Wednesday night. Kyle Hines added 18 points and 12 rebounds and Oleksiak made eight of the 10 shots in helping the Spartans (7-4) win their fourth straight. Kendall Toney added 11 points for UNC Greensboro, which shot 49 percent and made seven of their 16 attempts from 3-point range. Nate Bowie had 20 points and Durrell Nevels added 15 for Central Arkansas (10-4), which trailed just 46-37 at halftime before the Spartans outscored the Bears 34-25 in the final 20 minutes.
